Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.72,0:00:02.14,English,,0,0,0,,Good morning YouTube.\N{\rChinese}早安，YouTube。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.24,0:00:06.16,English,,0,0,0,,Professor Chiang here with another video.\N{\rChinese}钟江教授在此，带来新视频。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.38,0:00:10.04,English,,0,0,0,,Now some of you in the comment section have\N{\rChinese}现在你们中有些人在评论区……
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.04,0:00:14.26,English,,0,0,0,,been asking me why World War III has not started.\N{\rChinese}有人问我为什么三战未爆发。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.68,0:00:18.26,English,,0,0,0,,Why the conflict between the United States\N{\rChinese}为什么美国与伊朗的冲突。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.26,0:00:20.26,English,,0,0,0,,and Iran has abated.\N{\rChinese}与伊朗已缓解。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.78,0:00:23.02,English,,0,0,0,,The answer is because\N{\rChinese}答案是因为
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.02,0:00:26.84,English,,0,0,0,,modern warfare is hybrid warfare.\N{\rChinese}现代战争是混合战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.84,0:00:29.60,English,,0,0,0,,9% of warfare you will not see.\N{\rChinese}9%的战争你看不到。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.80,0:00:32.56,English,,0,0,0,,So much of warfare nowadays is informational,\N{\rChinese}如今战争的很大一部分是信息战，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.94,0:00:37.48,English,,0,0,0,,controlling the media narrative, electronic cyber warfare, psychological,\N{\rChinese}控制媒体叙事、电子网络战、心理战，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.90,0:00:41.20,English,,0,0,0,,weakening the will of the people to fight you,\N{\rChinese}削弱人们战斗意志。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.40,0:00:44.68,English,,0,0,0,,and covert ops, economic sabotage,\N{\rChinese}和秘密行动、经济破坏，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.94,0:00:47.00,English,,0,0,0,,imposing sanctions,\N{\rChinese}施加制裁，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.34,0:00:51.42,English,,0,0,0,,trying to assassinate the leaders of Iran.\N{\rChinese}试图暗杀伊朗领袖。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.68,0:00:54.32,English,,0,0,0,,So the United States and\N{\rChinese}于是美国和以色列都已投身于战争政策。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.32,0:00:56.82,English,,0,0,0,,Israel are committed to a policy of war.\N{\rChinese}一个伊朗政权更迭。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.82,0:01:00.20,English,,0,0,0,,A regime change in Iran.\N{\rChinese}A regime changein Iran.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.74,0:01:05.30,English,,0,0,0,,Ideally, they would like to assassinate the Ayatollah Khomeini\N{\rChinese}理想中，他们想暗杀霍梅尼阿亚图拉
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.30,0:01:09.84,English,,0,0,0,,because that would trigger a succession crisis in Iran.\N{\rChinese}因为这会在伊朗引发继任危机
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.19,0:01:13.96,English,,0,0,0,,Right now their main strategy is\N{\rChinese}目前他们的主要策略是
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.96,0:01:19.52,English,,0,0,0,,to decrease the legitimacy of the regime in Iran.\N{\rChinese}降低伊朗政权的合法性。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.84,0:01:21.50,English,,0,0,0,,And the best way to do that\N{\rChinese}最佳做法是……
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.50,0:01:26.80,English,,0,0,0,,is to decrease the capacity of the states.\N{\rChinese}就是降低各国的能力。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.82,0:01:28.78,English,,0,0,0,,to deliver basic services.\N{\rChinese}提供基本服务。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.50,0:01:31.18,English,,0,0,0,,For example, water.\N{\rChinese}例如，供水。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.74,0:01:35.96,English,,0,0,0,,So what's happening in Tehran right now, a city of 10 million, is there's a water shortage.\N{\rChinese}所以现在德黑兰这座一千万人口的城市正面临缺水。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.72,0:01:40.44,English,,0,0,0,,Because of heat, because\N{\rChinese}因为热，因而
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.44,0:01:42.62,English,,0,0,0,,of economic sanctions, because of overpopulation,\N{\rChinese}因经济制裁，因而
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.96,0:01:47.76,English,,0,0,0,,Tehran is having problems ensuring water supply to its people.\N{\rChinese}因人口过多，因而
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.40,0:01:51.38,English,,0,0,0,,You can bet good money\N{\rChinese}你可以打赌好几百美元
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.38,0:01:54.30,English,,0,0,0,,that the Israelis and Americans will take advantage of that\N{\rChinese}以色方和美方会利用这一点
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.30,0:01:56.80,English,,0,0,0,,to engage in economic sabotage.\N{\rChinese}去进行经济破坏
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.94,0:01:59.24,English,,0,0,0,,Basically trying to destroy as much of\N{\rChinese}基本上是想把伊朗的关键水利设施尽量摧毁。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.24,0:02:03.18,English,,0,0,0,,Iran's critical water infrastructure as possible.\N{\rChinese}他们想基本上制造一次饥荒，一场旱灾。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.44,0:02:07.82,English,,0,0,0,,They would want to basically create a famine, a drought.\N{\rChinese}They would want to basicallycreate a famine, a drought.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.52,0:02:12.00,English,,0,0,0,,Now the irony of that is that\N{\rChinese}现在的讽刺是
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.00,0:02:14.10,English,,0,0,0,,by engaging in this economic sabotage,\N{\rChinese}通过进行这场经济破坏
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.20,0:02:17.44,English,,0,0,0,,the Iranian\N{\rChinese}伊朗的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.08,0:02:24.06,English,,0,0,0,,people will develop a greater resolve for to resist.\N{\rChinese}人们会形成更强的抵抗决心。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.94,0:02:28.02,English,,0,0,0,,And once the resolve,\N{\rChinese}一旦决心，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.24,0:02:32.64,English,,0,0,0,,once the will to fight has been increased to a certain level,\N{\rChinese}一旦战斗意志提升到一定程度，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.88,0:02:37.08,English,,0,0,0,,then the Iranian government can close off the Strait of Hormuz,\N{\rChinese}然后伊朗政府可以封锁霍尔木兹海峡，随后美国陆军将会进攻。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.34,0:02:40.30,English,,0,0,0,,which would compel an American ground invasion.\N{\rChinese}如果美国真的这么做，美国将派遣陆军。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.78,0:02:43.76,English,,0,0,0,,And if America were to do that, America would send in ground troops,\N{\rChinese}And if America were to do that, America would send in ground troops,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.96,0:02:46.38,English,,0,0,0,,and as I've said in multiple videos before,\N{\rChinese}如我在之前多段视频中所说，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.66,0:02:51.12,English,,0,0,0,,the American military would lose this war.\N{\rChinese}美国军方将在这场战争中失利。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.36,0:02:57.20,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so that's how I see the war developing over the next few months.\N{\rChinese}好了，这就是我对未来几个月战争发展的看法。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.74,0:03:03.14,English,,0,0,0,,Today I want to talk about what the future is going to look like next 10 -20 years.\N{\rChinese}今天我想谈谈未来10到20年会是什么样子。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.40,0:03:05.60,English,,0,0,0,,I want to take everything we've learned so far and\N{\rChinese}我想把到目前为止学到的全部内容，
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.60,0:03:10.70,English,,0,0,0,,combine it into a grand thesis about how the world will develop.\N{\rChinese}合成一个宏大的论点，说明世界将如何发展。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.04,0:03:13.56,English,,0,0,0,,And the argument I want to make to you today is that\N{\rChinese}我今天想给你们说的论点是，
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.56,0:03:16.64,English,,0,0,0,,escatology drives geopolitics.\N{\rChinese}末世论推动着地缘政治。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.80,0:03:19.26,English,,0,0,0,,And to make this argument I'm going to ask three questions.\N{\rChinese}为展开这个论点，我将提出三个问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.76,0:03:23.44,English,,0,0,0,,First question is, why are escatologists so compelling?\N{\rChinese}第一问是，为什么末世论者如此吸引人？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.98,0:03:26.36,English,,0,0,0,,Second question is what are\N{\rChinese}第二问是，什么是……
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.36,0:03:30.06,English,,0,0,0,,the major eschatological traditions\N{\rChinese}第三问是，主要的末世论传统是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.06,0:03:33.46,English,,0,0,0,,and how do they converge together? And\N{\rChinese}以及它们是如何相互汇聚的？然后
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.46,0:03:36.94,English,,0,0,0,,the third question is based on these convergence\N{\rChinese}第三个问题基于这些汇聚点，
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.94,0:03:39.78,English,,0,0,0,,points what can we predict about the future?\N{\rChinese}我们能预测未来会怎样？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.56,0:03:42.76,English,,0,0,0,,Right so let's look at the first question which\N{\rChinese}好的，先看第一个问题：为什么末世论如此吸引人？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.76,0:03:45.70,English,,0,0,0,,is why are eschatologies so compelling?\N{\rChinese}正如我之前所说，末世论之所以吸引人？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.94,0:03:49.40,English,,0,0,0,,And as I've said before eschatologies are compelling\N{\rChinese}因为它们是叙述，捕捉人类想象。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.40,0:03:52.78,English,,0,0,0,,because they are narratives that\N{\rChinese}因为它们是叙述，捕捉人类想象。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.78,0:03:54.64,English,,0,0,0,,capture the human imagination.\N{\rChinese}它们回答了三个基本问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.16,0:03:56.86,English,,0,0,0,,They answer three fundamental questions.\N{\rChinese}They answer three fundamental questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.36,0:03:58.62,English,,0,0,0,,Where do we come from?\N{\rChinese}我们从哪里来？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.90,0:04:01.32,English,,0,0,0,,What are we doing here? Where are we going?\N{\rChinese}我们在这里做什么？我们要去哪里？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.44,0:04:03.80,English,,0,0,0,,It's a complete story on to itself.\N{\rChinese}它是一个完整的自足故事。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.08,0:04:07.94,English,,0,0,0,,You can think of eschatologies as scripts really.\N{\rChinese}你可以把末世论想象成真正的剧本。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.74,0:04:11.96,English,,0,0,0,,Scripts that have a momentum of their own.\N{\rChinese}剧本拥有自己的动量。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.24,0:04:15.64,English,,0,0,0,,Scripts that allow for unconscious coordination.\N{\rChinese}剧本允许无意识的协调。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.06,0:04:17.54,English,,0,0,0,,So what are the main characteristics of eschatology? Scripts that\N{\rChinese}那么，末世论的主要特征是什么？剧本为个体提供了表演的角色。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.54,0:04:21.62,English,,0,0,0,,present roles for individuals to audition for.\N{\rChinese}于是，只是参与剧本就行。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.86,0:04:25.58,English,,0,0,0,,So just by participating in a script\N{\rChinese}So just by participating in a script
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.58,0:04:30.04,English,,0,0,0,,you are helping the eschatology progress forward.\N{\rChinese}你正在帮助末世论向前推进。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.52,0:04:34.26,English,,0,0,0,,And to understand why eschatologies are\N{\rChinese}并且要理解为什么末世论如此强大，请记住博弈理论的普遍定律。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.26,0:04:39.26,English,,0,0,0,,so powerful please remember the universal law of game theory.\N{\rChinese}so powerful please remember the universal law of game theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.56,0:04:41.64,English,,0,0,0,,In a previous video I discussed\N{\rChinese}在之前的视频里我谈到了
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.64,0:04:45.58,English,,0,0,0,,how people win in the game\N{\rChinese}人们如何在游戏中获胜
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.58,0:04:48.54,English,,0,0,0,,and how they compete for the game.\N{\rChinese}以及他们如何竞争这个游戏
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.08,0:04:52.02,English,,0,0,0,,So let me tell you how people compete for the game.\N{\rChinese}让我来告诉你们人们是如何竞争这场游戏的。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.02,0:04:54.36,English,,0,0,0,,So let me tell you how people compete for the game. So let me tell you how people compete for the game.\N{\rChinese}让我来告诉你们人们是如何竞争这场游戏的。让我来告诉你们人们是如何竞争这场游戏的。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.38,0:04:57.02,English,,0,0,0,,So let me tell you how people compete for the game.\N{\rChinese}让我来告诉你们人们是如何竞争这场游戏的。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.02,0:04:58.80,English,,0,0,0,,So let me tell you how people compete for the game. So let me tell you how people compete for So let me tell you how people compete for the game.\N{\rChinese}让我来告诉你们人们是如何竞争这场游戏的。让我来告诉你们人们是如何竞争这场游戏的。让我来告诉你们人们是如何竞争这场游戏的。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.80,0:05:01.12,English,,0,0,0,,So let me tell you how people compete for the game.\N{\rChinese}让我来告诉你们人们是如何竞争这场游戏的。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.12,0:05:02.76,English,,0,0,0,,So let me tell you how people compete for the game.\N{\rChinese}让我来告诉你们人们是如何竞争这场游戏的。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.06,0:05:07.24,English,,0,0,0,,So let me tell you how people compete for the game.\N{\rChinese}让我来告诉你们人们是如何竞争这场游戏的。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.24,0:05:09.76,English,,0,0,0,,So let me tell you how people compete for the game.\N{\rChinese}让我来告诉你们人们是如何竞争这场游戏的。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.76,0:05:15.66,English,,0,0,0,,So let me tell you how people compete for the game.\N{\rChinese}让我来告诉你们人们是如何竞争这场游戏的。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.66,0:05:16.90,English,,0,0,0,,cooperation because\N{\rChinese}合作因为
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.90,0:05:20.94,English,,0,0,0,,everyone's fighting for his or her best self -interest.\N{\rChinese}每个人都在为自己的最佳利益而战斗。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.40,0:05:25.56,English,,0,0,0,,But with an unconscious coordination, which is what an eschatology provides,\N{\rChinese}但有一种无意识的协调，这正是末世论所提供的。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.10,0:05:28.98,English,,0,0,0,,that allows for secrecy,\N{\rChinese}那让人们可以保密，
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.00,0:05:31.44,English,,0,0,0,,possible deniability, and\N{\rChinese}可能的可否认性，和
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.44,0:05:33.88,English,,0,0,0,,frictionless cooperation.\N{\rChinese}无摩擦的合作。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.40,0:05:36.64,English,,0,0,0,,And that's why eschatologists are so powerful.\N{\rChinese}于是，末世论者才显得如此强大。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.70,0:05:40.46,English,,0,0,0,,Now some of you may hear this and\N{\rChinese}现在你们中的一些人可能会听到这句话并
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.46,0:05:43.96,English,,0,0,0,,think this doesn't make any sense because it's really individual self -interest\N{\rChinese}觉得这根本毫无意义，因为它确实是个人自利。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.96,0:05:45.54,English,,0,0,0,,that motivates us.\N{\rChinese}那激励我们。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.96,0:05:49.10,English,,0,0,0,,And what's really important to understand is these things,\N{\rChinese}而真正重要的是要理解这些事，
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.28,0:05:53.58,English,,0,0,0,,eschatologies, and individual self -interest are not in conflict with each other.\N{\rChinese}末世论与个人自利并不相互冲突。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.68,0:05:55.60,English,,0,0,0,,In fact, they reinforce each other.\N{\rChinese}事实上，它们相互加强。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.96,0:05:58.76,English,,0,0,0,,Now in school you may be taught that\N{\rChinese}现在在学校里你可能会被教到
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.76,0:06:01.28,English,,0,0,0,,to succeed in life you have to work hard,\N{\rChinese}要在生活中成功，你必须努力工作。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.46,0:06:05.18,English,,0,0,0,,you have to be talented, you have to get good grades in school,\N{\rChinese}你要有才华，得在学校拿好成绩，并且要很聪明。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.36,0:06:07.28,English,,0,0,0,,and you have to be very intelligent.\N{\rChinese}当然那是我曾经相信的，我花了二三十年才意识到自己错了。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.52,0:06:12.08,English,,0,0,0,,Certainly that's what I believed and it took me 20 -30 years to recognize I was wrong.\N{\rChinese}Certainly that's what I believed and it took me 20 -30 years to recognize I was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.24,0:06:14.04,English,,0,0,0,,It's not what you know.\N{\rChinese}这不是你知道的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.14,0:06:15.20,English,,0,0,0,,It's who you are. It's who you know.\N{\rChinese}是你是谁。是你认识的人。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.70,0:06:18.04,English,,0,0,0,,To succeed in life you have to be\N{\rChinese}要在生活中成功，你必须是…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.04,0:06:23.10,English,,0,0,0,,able to work with others in a secretive, unconscious,\N{\rChinese}能够与他人秘密、无意识地合作
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.78,0:06:28.98,English,,0,0,0,,coordinated manner in order to achieve certain goals.\N{\rChinese}以协调的方式按顺序实现特定目标。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.70,0:06:33.32,English,,0,0,0,,And that's what eschatology provides.\N{\rChinese}这就是预言学所提供的。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.78,0:06:36.76,English,,0,0,0,,So when you subscribe to an eschatology, when you commit to an eschatology,\N{\rChinese}当你订阅一个终末论时，当你投身于终末论时，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.96,0:06:40.52,English,,0,0,0,,others will help you achieve wealth\N{\rChinese}其他人会帮助你实现财富。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.52,0:06:41.82,English,,0,0,0,,and power.\N{\rChinese}和权力。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.30,0:06:44.80,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So that's why I'm so proud of you.\N{\rChinese}好的？所以这就是我为你感到自豪的原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.80,0:06:48.52,English,,0,0,0,,Thank you. Good job.\N{\rChinese}谢谢。干得好。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.80,0:06:50.82,English,,0,0,0,,Good job. Good job.\N{\rChinese}干得好。干得好。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.18,0:06:54.06,English,,0,0,0,,Good job. Good job. Good job. Good job.\N{\rChinese}干得好。干得好。干得好。干得好。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.64,0:06:56.18,English,,0,0,0,,Good job. Good job.\N{\rChinese}干得好。干得好。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.72,0:06:59.32,English,,0,0,0,,Good job. Good job.\N{\rChinese}干得好。干得好。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.32,0:07:00.54,English,,0,0,0,,Good job. Good job. Good job. Good job. Good job. Good job.\N{\rChinese}干得好。干得好。干得好。干得好。干得好。干得好。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.54,0:07:03.10,English,,0,0,0,,Good job. Good job. Good job. Good job. Good job. Good job.\N{\rChinese}干得好。干得好。干得好。干得好。干得好。干得好。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.44,0:07:05.28,English,,0,0,0,,Good job. Good job.\N{\rChinese}干得好。干得好。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.04,0:07:07.00,English,,0,0,0,,Good job.\N{\rChinese}干得好。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.76,0:07:16.20,English,,0,0,0,,Good job. I want to remind everyone of three caveats.\N{\rChinese}干得好。我想提醒大家三个注意点。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.32,0:07:20.81,English,,0,0,0,,The first caveat is that within each religion,\N{\rChinese}第一个注意点是每个宗教内部都有……
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.84,0:07:26.32,English,,0,0,0,,eschatology is only a minority extreme view.\N{\rChinese}末世论只是少数极端观点。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.84,0:07:30.22,English,,0,0,0,,Only a small minority of religious\N{\rChinese}只有少数宗教
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.22,0:07:34.12,English,,0,0,0,,devotees will actually believe in the eschatology.\N{\rChinese}信徒才会真正相信末世论。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.24,0:07:38.76,English,,0,0,0,,That's the first caveat. The second caveat is\N{\rChinese}那是第一个注意点。第二个注意点是
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.76,0:07:44.30,English,,0,0,0,,that there's tremendous diversity within each eschatology.\N{\rChinese}每个末世论内部都有巨大的多样性。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.62,0:07:48.08,English,,0,0,0,,You can interpret the eschatology allegorically,\N{\rChinese}你可以把末世论解作比喻，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.96,0:07:54.14,English,,0,0,0,,which is to say it's compelling you to a path of personal redemption\N{\rChinese}这就是说它把你推向个人救赎之路
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.14,0:07:56.28,English,,0,0,0,,and salvation in order to improve the world.\N{\rChinese}并以救赎为序，改善世界。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.48,0:07:59.40,English,,0,0,0,,Or you can interpret it literally, which is that\N{\rChinese}或者你可以按字面解释，即是……
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.40,0:08:01.90,English,,0,0,0,,this is a true prophecy and\N{\rChinese}这是一条真实预言，且
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.90,0:08:04.98,English,,0,0,0,,everything in it will happen in order for\N{\rChinese}其中的一切都将按顺序发生
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.98,0:08:08.94,English,,0,0,0,,the world to end or for the world to become a better place.\N{\rChinese}世界终结或变为更好之地
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.54,0:08:11.12,English,,0,0,0,,And also, the second caveat is that\N{\rChinese}第二个要点是
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.58,0:08:16.14,English,,0,0,0,,there are different sequencing of events and different interpretations in the eschatology.\N{\rChinese}在末世论中，事件的顺序和解释各不相同。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.38,0:08:17.90,English,,0,0,0,,So that's the second caveat.\N{\rChinese}所以那是第二个要点。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.26,0:08:22.00,English,,0,0,0,,Eschatologies within each tradition are very diverse.\N{\rChinese}各传统中的末世论非常多样。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.14,0:08:26.40,English,,0,0,0,,And the third caveat is that\N{\rChinese}第三个要点是
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.40,0:08:28.66,English,,0,0,0,,eschatologies are dynamic.\N{\rChinese}末世论是动态的。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.12,0:08:33.50,English,,0,0,0,,And the reason why is eschatologies are in conflict,\N{\rChinese}原因是末世论相互冲突
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.58,0:08:35.44,English,,0,0,0,,are in competition in communication\N{\rChinese}在传播中相互竞争
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.14,0:08:37.36,English,,0,0,0,,with different eschatologies.\N{\rChinese}与不同的末世论相结合。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.66,0:08:41.08,English,,0,0,0,,Think of eschatologies as stories,\N{\rChinese}把末世论想象成故事，
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.58,0:08:44.80,English,,0,0,0,,that are trying to be the best possible story\N{\rChinese}它们试图成为最好的故事
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.17,0:08:49.14,English,,0,0,0,,in order to capture the imagination of their believers.\N{\rChinese}按顺序捕捉信徒的想象。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.38,0:08:52.82,English,,0,0,0,,And to do that, they're going to incorporate the best elements\N{\rChinese}为此，他们将融合最佳元素。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.82,0:08:56.18,English,,0,0,0,,from different eschatologies into their own.\N{\rChinese}从不同的末世论转化为自己的。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.38,0:08:58.84,English,,0,0,0,,And that's why so many of these eschatologies,\N{\rChinese}这就是为什么这么多的末世论，
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.08,0:09:01.80,English,,0,0,0,,they follow similar pattern because they've been learning\N{\rChinese}它们遵循相似模式，因为它们相互学习并适应。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.80,0:09:05.81,English,,0,0,0,,and adapting from each other.\N{\rChinese}并相互学习并适应。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.64,0:09:10.50,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So having said these three caveats, let's go into the six,\N{\rChinese}好的。说完这三点后，让我们进入六大主要末世论。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.58,0:09:13.64,English,,0,0,0,,the major eschatological traditions.\N{\rChinese}第一大类是祆罗波斯教。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.08,0:09:19.40,English,,0,0,0,,And I'm going to focus on the most extreme version of each tradition,\N{\rChinese}我将聚焦每个传统最极端的版本，
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.64,0:09:21.54,English,,0,0,0,,because according to game theory,\N{\rChinese}因为按博弈论的说法，
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.18,0:09:23.80,English,,0,0,0,,it's the fanatics who matter.\N{\rChinese}是热心者才重要。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.04,0:09:26.10,English,,0,0,0,,It's the fanatics who are the most energetic, who\N{\rChinese}是热心者最有活力，最有热情，才是……
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.10,0:09:29.96,English,,0,0,0,,are the most committed to achieving the eschatology.\N{\rChinese}他们最投入实现末世论。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.38,0:09:34.20,English,,0,0,0,,So the first eschatology is Zoroastrianism,\N{\rChinese}于是第一个末世论是祆罗波斯教。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.26,0:09:36.30,English,,0,0,0,,which was the original eschatology.\N{\rChinese}它是最初的末世论。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.98,0:09:38.80,English,,0,0,0,,In the Zoroastrian tradition,\N{\rChinese}在祆罗波斯传统中，
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.16,0:09:44.34,English,,0,0,0,,there's the world is divided, there's the world is divided into good and evil,\N{\rChinese}世界被分为好与坏，光与暗，真与假。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.28,0:09:49.84,English,,0,0,0,,the light and the darkness, the truth and the lie.\N{\rChinese}在日子终末，…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.42,0:09:52.26,English,,0,0,0,,And at the end of the days,\N{\rChinese}And at the end of the days,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.64,0:09:55.64,English,,0,0,0,,there'll be a final battle between these two cosmic forces.\N{\rChinese}将会有一次这两种宇宙力量的终极之战。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.74,0:10:00.06,English,,0,0,0,,And as humans, we must choose which side to fight for.\N{\rChinese}于是人类必须选择站在哪一方。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.28,0:10:05.02,English,,0,0,0,,At the end of this battle, when good has triumphed, there'll be a day of judgment.\N{\rChinese}战斗结束，善势胜时，将迎来审判之日。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.38,0:10:07.66,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. And this structure,\N{\rChinese}好的。这个结构，
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.90,0:10:10.68,English,,0,0,0,,this cosmology heavily influenced,\N{\rChinese}这个宇宙观深受影响，
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.58,0:10:15.72,English,,0,0,0,,uh, Judaism. And so in the Judaic tradition,\N{\rChinese}呃，犹太教。于是犹太传统中，
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.54,0:10:18.50,English,,0,0,0,,because Jews have been persecuted for,\N{\rChinese}因为犹太人被迫害了千年，
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.10,0:10:21.18,English,,0,0,0,,um, thousands of years,\N{\rChinese}呃，几千年，
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.42,0:10:26.36,English,,0,0,0,,they believe that eventually a messiah of war will come to them.\N{\rChinese}他们相信最终会有一位战争的弥赛亚来临。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.98,0:10:29.76,English,,0,0,0,,And he will lead the Jews\N{\rChinese}他将带领犹太人
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.76,0:10:33.72,English,,0,0,0,,to victory against all the enemies.\N{\rChinese}并取得对所有敌人的胜利
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.40,0:10:37.08,English,,0,0,0,,He will reconstitute the nation of Israel and\N{\rChinese}他将重组以色列民族
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.08,0:10:39.90,English,,0,0,0,,bring back all the Jews from the diaspora.\N{\rChinese}把犹太人从散居中召回
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.02,0:10:42.68,English,,0,0,0,,He will build the third temple and\N{\rChinese}他将建造第三座圣殿
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.68,0:10:45.56,English,,0,0,0,,he will usher in the messianic age\N{\rChinese}他将开启弥赛亚时代
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.13,0:10:48.38,English,,0,0,0,,of peace, prosperity,\N{\rChinese}和平、繁荣、真理、正义。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.82,0:10:50.74,English,,0,0,0,,truth, justice.\N{\rChinese}对吧？那就是犹太传统。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.39,0:10:53.36,English,,0,0,0,,Right? That's the Judaic tradition.\N{\rChinese}Right? That's the Judaic tradition.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.94,0:10:59.70,English,,0,0,0,,The Judaic tradition went on to influence the Christian Zionists or the Protestant tradition.\N{\rChinese}犹太传统继续影响基督教犹太复国者或新教派。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.00,0:11:03.90,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So, uh, the Protestants believed that\N{\rChinese}好的。所以，呃，新教派认为……
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.29,0:11:06.48,English,,0,0,0,,the messiah is Jesus and he's already come.\N{\rChinese}弥赛亚是耶稣，他已经来临。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.05,0:11:11.78,English,,0,0,0,,So in order to usher in his second coming, certain conditions have to be met.\N{\rChinese}为迎接第二次降临，必须满足若干条件。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.32,0:11:16.62,English,,0,0,0,,First condition is the nation of Israel has to be reconstituted, and it was in 1948.\N{\rChinese}第一条条件是以色列民族国家必须重建，且已于1948年完成。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.58,0:11:22.62,English,,0,0,0,,Um, then the third temple has to be built\N{\rChinese}随后，第三座圣殿需再度建造。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.06,0:11:26.66,English,,0,0,0,,and there has to be a war, uh, of Gog and Magog.\N{\rChinese}并且必有戈格与玛各之战。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.84,0:11:28.12,English,,0,0,0,,The Antichrist has to appear.\N{\rChinese}反基督将会出现。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.32,0:11:30.96,English,,0,0,0,,And once these conditions are met, then\N{\rChinese}当这些条件满足后，
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.96,0:11:35.84,English,,0,0,0,,to save his people, Jesus will descend from heaven on a cloud,\N{\rChinese}为拯救其民，耶稣将从云中降临天上，
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.10,0:11:39.16,English,,0,0,0,,destroy all his enemies, and usher in a millennium\N{\rChinese}击败其敌人，开启千年和平、繁荣、真理、正义与安宁。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.16,0:11:42.16,English,,0,0,0,,of peace, prosperity, truth, justice, and peace. and\N{\rChinese}of peace, prosperity, truth, justice, and peace. and
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.16,0:11:47.26,English,,0,0,0,,justice before the final judgment.\N{\rChinese}在最终审判之前的正义。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.70,0:11:50.70,English,,0,0,0,,When Jesus returns, there would be a rapture where\N{\rChinese}当耶稣再来时，将有一次欢腾，届时所有基督徒将立即升天。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.70,0:11:55.18,English,,0,0,0,,all Christians will immediately ascend to heaven.\N{\rChinese}all Christians will immediately ascend to heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.52,0:11:58.38,English,,0,0,0,,So that's the Christian Zionist Protestant tradition.\N{\rChinese}于是就是基督教犹太复国新教派的传统。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.14,0:12:01.16,English,,0,0,0,,Um, and again, this is the most extreme form\N{\rChinese}嗯，再说一次，这就是该传统的最极端形式。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.56,0:12:03.10,English,,0,0,0,,of that tradition.\N{\rChinese}这就是该传统的最极端形式。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.62,0:12:07.56,English,,0,0,0,,Then you have the Islamic tradition, which\N{\rChinese}然后你会看到伊斯兰传统，
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.56,0:12:10.92,English,,0,0,0,,is based both on the Judaic and the Christian tradition.\N{\rChinese}它既基于犹太传统，也基于基督传统。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.92,0:12:12.62,English,,0,0,0,,Um, and then you have the Islamic tradition, which is based both on the Judaic and the Christian tradition. Um, and again, this is the most extreme form of that tradition. Um, and again, this is the most extreme form of that tradition. And it's very similar.\N{\rChinese}嗯，再说一次，伊斯兰传统既基于犹太和基督传统，且是其最极端形式，且非常相似。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.94,0:12:14.60,English,,0,0,0,,Um, so\N{\rChinese}嗯，算是
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.60,0:12:18.42,English,,0,0,0,,the Muslims believe that\N{\rChinese}穆斯林认为
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.36,0:12:21.94,English,,0,0,0,,after an age of tribulation, when\N{\rChinese}在经历一段苦难期后，
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.94,0:12:25.14,English,,0,0,0,,the world has turned its back on God, when the world is divided,\N{\rChinese}世界已背向上帝，万物分裂之时，
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.30,0:12:29.04,English,,0,0,0,,um, a great leader\N{\rChinese}嗯，一位伟大领袖
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.70,0:12:32.54,English,,0,0,0,,will come to unify the people\N{\rChinese}将会出现，统一众人
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.04,0:12:34.62,English,,0,0,0,,and lead the people,\N{\rChinese}并领领众人，
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.30,0:12:38.22,English,,0,0,0,,uh, to victory in the war of Gog and Magog.\N{\rChinese}嗬，去赢得古格与玛古的战争胜利。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.40,0:12:41.12,English,,0,0,0,,Uh, Gog and Magog is interpreted as the Antichrist.\N{\rChinese}嗬，古格与玛古被解释为末世之敌。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.12,0:12:43.18,English,,0,0,0,,Uh, Gog and Magog is interpreted as the Antichrist.\N{\rChinese}嗗，古格与玛古被解释为末世之敌。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.18,0:12:45.00,English,,0,0,0,,And Gog and Magog can be interpreted as maybe Western civilization\N{\rChinese}嗗，古格与玛古也可解释为西方文明。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.66,0:12:49.08,English,,0,0,0,,for its materialism, but it could also be a certain force.\N{\rChinese}嗗，因其物质主义，但亦可视为某种力量。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.30,0:12:52.12,English,,0,0,0,,So, for example, maybe, uh, the city of London.\N{\rChinese}比如说，呃，伦敦这座城市。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.52,0:12:56.20,English,,0,0,0,,Um, so that's the Islamic tradition.\N{\rChinese}嗯，所以那就是伊斯兰传统。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.52,0:13:00.36,English,,0,0,0,,Then you have the Orthodox tradition, which is what we talked about in the last video.\N{\rChinese}然后你就有正教传统，这就是我们在上一段视频里讨论的内容。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.48,0:13:04.06,English,,0,0,0,,The Orthodox tradition believes that Moscow is the third Rome.\N{\rChinese}正教传统认为莫斯科是第三罗马。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.14,0:13:07.20,English,,0,0,0,,It has a destiny to restore the Byzantine Empire.\N{\rChinese}它有使命恢复拜占庭帝国。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.48,0:13:10.54,English,,0,0,0,,And to achieve this destiny, uh, Moscow,\N{\rChinese}为实现此使命，呃，莫斯科，
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.54,0:13:12.68,English,,0,0,0,,Moscow, Moscow, will fight a war with Turkey.\N{\rChinese}莫斯科，莫斯科，将与土耳其开战。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.84,0:13:14.48,English,,0,0,0,,It will destroy Turkey. And then\N{\rChinese}它将消灭土耳其。然后
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.48,0:13:17.82,English,,0,0,0,,return the Greeks to Constantinople,\N{\rChinese}把希腊人送回君士坦丁堡。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.08,0:13:21.36,English,,0,0,0,,thus restoring the Byzantine Empire and\N{\rChinese}于是恢复拜占庭帝国，并统一正教世界。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.36,0:13:25.60,English,,0,0,0,,thus unifying the Orthodox Christian world.\N{\rChinese}现在，真正有趣的事是……
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.36,0:13:28.72,English,,0,0,0,,Now, what's really interesting is that\N{\rChinese}Now, what's reallyinteresting is that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.72,0:13:31.22,English,,0,0,0,,there is a geoblical theorist named Alexander Dugin,\N{\rChinese}有一位地缘史学家叫亚历山大·杜金，
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.34,0:13:35.36,English,,0,0,0,,who's turned this eschatology into a master plan\N{\rChinese}他把这场末世论变成了一个主计划
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.72,0:13:37.52,English,,0,0,0,,for Vladimir Putin to implement.\N{\rChinese}供弗拉基米尔·普京来实施。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.94,0:13:40.34,English,,0,0,0,,If you don't know who Alexander Dugin is,\N{\rChinese}如果你还不知道亚历山大·杜金是谁，
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.54,0:13:43.90,English,,0,0,0,,you have to, um, watch his interviews.\N{\rChinese}你得先看他的访谈。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.04,0:13:47.64,English,,0,0,0,,You have to read his books. Because he's probably the most important\N{\rChinese}你得读他的书。因为他大概是最重要的。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.90,0:13:50.76,English,,0,0,0,,geostrategic thinker we have today.\N{\rChinese}我们今天拥有的地缘战略思想家。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.00,0:13:53.94,English,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna put his videos and his books in the description below,\N{\rChinese}我会把他的影片和书放在下面的描述里，
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.14,0:13:58.76,English,,0,0,0,,so please make sure you spend the time to actually research him.\N{\rChinese}请务必花时间去研究他。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.88,0:14:02.78,English,,0,0,0,,Because so much of what he says helps us understand the world as it is today\N{\rChinese}因为他所说的内容帮助我们理解今天的世界以及未来的发展。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.42,0:14:05.64,English,,0,0,0,,and how the world will develop over time.\N{\rChinese}于是，在1997年，…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.30,0:14:07.64,English,,0,0,0,,So, in 1997,\N{\rChinese}So, in 1997,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.04,0:14:11.92,English,,0,0,0,,uh, Dugin published a book called, Foundations of Geopolitics,\N{\rChinese}呃，杜金出版了一本叫《地缘政治基础》的书，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.98,0:14:13.96,English,,0,0,0,,where he describes his master plan\N{\rChinese}在书中他描述了他的总计划
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.50,0:14:16.10,English,,0,0,0,,for how, um,\N{\rChinese}来说明他是怎么做的，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.24,0:14:19.98,English,,0,0,0,,Moscow can restore the Byzantine Empire.\N{\rChinese}莫斯科能恢复拜占庭帝国。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.90,0:14:24.70,English,,0,0,0,,So, what he understands is\N{\rChinese}于是，他的理解是
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.70,0:14:30.42,English,,0,0,0,,that for the longest time, whoever controls the seas controls the world,\N{\rChinese}长久以来，谁掌握海权，谁掌握世界。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.52,0:14:33.54,English,,0,0,0,,because most trade was done through sea.\N{\rChinese}因为大部分贸易都通过海路完成。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.20,0:14:38.22,English,,0,0,0,,But in a time of nation states, in a time of railways,\N{\rChinese}但在民族国家时代，在铁路时代，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.04,0:14:43.64,English,,0,0,0,,if one power can unite the Europe\N{\rChinese}如果一个力量能统一欧洲
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.64,0:14:46.92,English,,0,0,0,,and Asian continents into the Eurasian continent,\N{\rChinese}并把亚洲大陆纳入欧亚大陆，然后该力量可消除海权
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.32,0:14:50.04,English,,0,0,0,,then that power can negate sea power\N{\rChinese}然后该力量可消除海权
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.22,0:14:54.04,English,,0,0,0,,and, uh, become the global hegemon.\N{\rChinese}并且成为全球霸权
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.22,0:14:57.22,English,,0,0,0,,And, uh, and that's why the British,\N{\rChinese}于是，英国，嗯，正是因为这个原因，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.86,0:14:59.96,English,,0,0,0,,the British Empire, are committed to two things.\N{\rChinese}英国帝国，已承诺两件事，
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.14,0:15:02.70,English,,0,0,0,,The first thing they're committed to is maintaining naval power.\N{\rChinese}首先，他们承诺保持海军力量。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.84,0:15:05.36,English,,0,0,0,,And the second thing they're committed to is ensuring that\N{\rChinese}并且他们承诺的第二件事是确保
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.36,0:15:09.62,English,,0,0,0,,no major power would arise in the Eurasian,\N{\rChinese}在欧亚心脏地带没有大国崛起。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.04,0:15:12.82,English,,0,0,0,,uh, heartland. And that's why, um,\N{\rChinese}这就是为什么，嗯，
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.96,0:15:15.64,English,,0,0,0,,the British basically provoked Germany into World War I,\N{\rChinese}英国基本上把德国逼入第一次世界大战，
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.78,0:15:18.86,English,,0,0,0,,because Germany was threatening to be this power.\N{\rChinese}因为德国正威胁要成为那股力量。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.12,0:15:21.10,English,,0,0,0,,And, and that's why, uh,\N{\rChinese}于是，嗯，
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.22,0:15:24.42,English,,0,0,0,,Britain is now afraid of Russia, because\N{\rChinese}英国现在害怕俄罗斯，因为
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.42,0:15:25.98,English,,0,0,0,,Russia is trying to be that\N{\rChinese}俄罗斯正试图成为那股力量，
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.98,0:15:30.12,English,,0,0,0,,power to unify the entire Eurasian heartland.\N{\rChinese}统一整个欧亚心脏地带。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.70,0:15:34.58,English,,0,0,0,,For Dugin, um, to unify the Eurasian heartland,\N{\rChinese}对杜金来说，嗯，要统一欧亚心脏地带，
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.80,0:15:37.88,English,,0,0,0,,uh, what Moscow needs to do is, first of all,\N{\rChinese}嗯，莫斯科需要做的第一件事是，
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.88,0:15:40.02,English,,0,0,0,,create the Berlin -Moscow border.\N{\rChinese}先建立柏林-莫斯科边界。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.04,0:15:42.48,English,,0,0,0,,It must create the Moscow axis to reconcile itself with Europe.\N{\rChinese}它必须创建莫斯科轴线，以便与欧洲调和。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.72,0:15:46.38,English,,0,0,0,,It must also create the Moscow\N{\rChinese}它还必须创建莫斯科-东京轴线，以便……
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.38,0:15:49.76,English,,0,0,0,,-Tokyo axis to reach out to, uh,\N{\rChinese}-Tokyo axis to reach out to, uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.30,0:15:51.86,English,,0,0,0,,uh, Southeast Asia.\N{\rChinese}嗯，东南亚。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.28,0:15:57.84,English,,0,0,0,,And also to create the Moscow terrain axis,\N{\rChinese}又要创建莫斯科地形轴线，
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.12,0:16:02.70,English,,0,0,0,,uh, to control the resources of the Middle East.\N{\rChinese}嗯，掌控中东资源。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.02,0:16:06.84,English,,0,0,0,,And by building this alliance, what Moscow is doing is not only,\N{\rChinese}并且通过组建此联盟，莫斯科所做的事不只是
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.86,0:16:08.94,English,,0,0,0,,not only restoring the Besson Empire, but\N{\rChinese}恢复贝松帝国，
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.94,0:16:12.10,English,,0,0,0,,it's also restoring the Pax Mongolica, the Mongol Empire.\N{\rChinese}也恢复了蒙古帝国的和平秩序
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.42,0:16:14.88,English,,0,0,0,,So, Moscow sees itself as the, um,\N{\rChinese}于是，莫斯科把自己视为，呃，
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.18,0:16:18.92,English,,0,0,0,,heirs to both the Besson Empire as well as the Mongolian Empire.\N{\rChinese}贝松帝国与蒙古帝国的继承者。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.86,0:16:23.68,English,,0,0,0,,Now, um, Dugin thinks this is entirely possible\N{\rChinese}现在，呃，杜金认为这完全可行。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.04,0:16:27.82,English,,0,0,0,,because, uh, the Iranians, the Japanese,\N{\rChinese}因为，呃，伊朗人、日本人、德国人都觉得被英美帝国轻视，呃，受辱。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.90,0:16:31.80,English,,0,0,0,,and the Germans all feel slighted, um,\N{\rChinese}因为，呃，伊朗人、日本人、德国人都觉得被英美帝国轻视，呃，受辱。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.74,0:16:35.50,English,,0,0,0,,humiliated by the Anglo -American Empire.\N{\rChinese}因为，呃，伊朗人、日本人、德国人都觉得被英美帝国轻视，呃，受辱。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.80,0:16:38.90,English,,0,0,0,,So, if you give them a choice between sticking with the\N{\rChinese}于是，如果给他们一个选择：继续留在英美帝国，还是加入新的俄罗斯联邦，给他们更多自由，他们会选择俄罗斯联邦。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.90,0:16:42.58,English,,0,0,0,,Anglo -American Empire or joining the new Russian Confederation,\N{\rChinese}现在，显然，英美帝国会对此计划作出反应，
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.86,0:16:47.64,English,,0,0,0,,where they'll be given more freedom, then they will opt for the Russian Confederation.\N{\rChinese}于是，对杜金来说，重要的是在美国内部制造混乱、分裂与冲突。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.16,0:16:49.66,English,,0,0,0,,So, that's the grand plan.\N{\rChinese}于是，这就是宏伟计划。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.92,0:16:54.52,English,,0,0,0,,Now, obviously, the Anglo -American Empire is gonna oppose this,\N{\rChinese}现在，显然，英美帝国会对此计划作出反应，
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.58,0:16:57.12,English,,0,0,0,,uh, plan. And so, for Dugin,\N{\rChinese}呃，计划。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.24,0:16:59.44,English,,0,0,0,,what's important is to create\N{\rChinese}重要的是制造内部混乱
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.00,0:17:02.90,English,,0,0,0,,internal chaos and dissent and\N{\rChinese}和分裂
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.90,0:17:05.28,English,,0,0,0,,conflict within America and\N{\rChinese}以及美国内部的冲突
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.28,0:17:08.50,English,,0,0,0,,within Britain to destroy the Anglo -American Empire.\N{\rChinese}在英国内部，消灭英美帝国。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.72,0:17:11.74,English,,0,0,0,,And that's already happening right now because, um,\N{\rChinese}而这已经在现在发生了，因为，呃，
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.88,0:17:16.16,English,,0,0,0,,you have Brexit in Britain, and now you have this mass immigration, which is threatening the British identity.\N{\rChinese}你有英国脱欧，随后又有大规模移民，威胁英国身份。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.48,0:17:19.94,English,,0,0,0,,In America, you have Donald Trump, who is proposing America first.\N{\rChinese}在美国，唐纳德·特朗普提出“美国优先”。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.14,0:17:21.62,English,,0,0,0,,So, all is gonna plan.\N{\rChinese}于是，一切都将按计划进行。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.06,0:17:24.98,English,,0,0,0,,This plan also recognizes that both Turkey\N{\rChinese}该计划也承认土耳其两者。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.98,0:17:30.84,English,,0,0,0,,and China are also enemies to the rise of this,\N{\rChinese}和中国也是这场欧亚统一崛起的敌人。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.06,0:17:34.20,English,,0,0,0,,um, Eurasian, uh, unification.\N{\rChinese}呃，然而正如我们在前一段视频里讨论的那样，
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.32,0:17:37.86,English,,0,0,0,,Um, but as we discussed in a previous video,\N{\rChinese}Um, but as we discussed in a previous video,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.52,0:17:41.34,English,,0,0,0,,Turkey itself is not very stable.\N{\rChinese}土耳其本身不太稳定。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.58,0:17:45.14,English,,0,0,0,,It's kept together, uh, for the political maneuvering of Erdogan.\N{\rChinese}它被维持在一起，呃，为埃尔多安的政治操作。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.78,0:17:48.76,English,,0,0,0,,Once he's gone, then all these ethnic tensions,\N{\rChinese}一旦他离开，所有这些民族紧张就会出现。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.58,0:17:52.52,English,,0,0,0,,these geopolitical tensions, these economic tensions that\N{\rChinese}这些地缘政治紧张，这些经济紧张
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.52,0:17:55.40,English,,0,0,0,,exist in Turkey will explode,\N{\rChinese}在土耳其出现的将会爆发
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.46,0:17:57.46,English,,0,0,0,,and it will overwhelm Turkey,\N{\rChinese}并且将把土耳其压垮
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.64,0:18:01.82,English,,0,0,0,,thus causing it to collapse, um, as a nation -state.\N{\rChinese}于是导致它崩溃，呃，成为一个民族国家。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.92,0:18:03.84,English,,0,0,0,,It will lose its coherence as a nation -state.\N{\rChinese}它将失去作为民族国家的连贯性。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.76,0:18:06.56,English,,0,0,0,,Dugin is not worried about China as well.\N{\rChinese}杜金也不太担心中国。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.76,0:18:10.66,English,,0,0,0,,He understands that, uh, he understands that Russia and China can never be allies,\N{\rChinese}他明白，呃，他明白俄罗斯和中国永远是盟友不到的
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.08,0:18:12.24,English,,0,0,0,,uh, because\N{\rChinese}呃，因为
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.24,0:18:17.22,English,,0,0,0,,China is too economic dependent on the Anglo -American Empire.\N{\rChinese}中国对英美帝国的经济依赖太大了
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.78,0:18:21.68,English,,0,0,0,,Basically, the point is, Russia has nothing to offer China.\N{\rChinese}基本上，重点是俄罗斯对中国没有任何可提供的东西。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.12,0:18:25.36,English,,0,0,0,,China is basically a manufacturing economy\N{\rChinese}中国基本上是一个制造业经济体。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.36,0:18:29.60,English,,0,0,0,,which must sell its goods to the Anglo -American Empire.\N{\rChinese}它必须把产品卖给英美帝国。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.82,0:18:32.84,English,,0,0,0,,Russia will, cannot absorb these goods.\N{\rChinese}俄罗斯将无法吸收这些货物。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.10,0:18:35.10,English,,0,0,0,,Um, at the same time,\N{\rChinese}呃，在同一时间，
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.85,0:18:37.62,English,,0,0,0,,there are a lot of internal contradictions\N{\rChinese}内部矛盾很多。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.98,0:18:39.18,English,,0,0,0,,in China.\N{\rChinese}在中国。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.70,0:18:44.08,English,,0,0,0,,I can tell you, as someone who lives in China for many, many decades,\N{\rChinese}我可以告诉你，作为一个在中国生活了许多几十年的居民，
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.52,0:18:47.78,English,,0,0,0,,China is not going to survive an economic catastrophe.\N{\rChinese}中国将无法在经济灾难中存活。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.16,0:18:51.16,English,,0,0,0,,It's not going to survive an ecological catastrophe.\N{\rChinese}它将无法在生态灾难中存活。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.52,0:18:54.38,English,,0,0,0,,In fact, its economy is,\N{\rChinese}事实上，它的经济是，
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.52,0:18:57.06,English,,0,0,0,,uh, propelling its, its,\N{\rChinese}呃，推动它的，的，
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.12,0:19:00.24,English,,0,0,0,,the nation to a ecological catastrophe.\N{\rChinese}民族国家陷入生态灾难。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.24,0:19:04.12,English,,0,0,0,,China is overpopulated, has very little resources,\N{\rChinese}中国人口众多，资源极少，
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.20,0:19:07.96,English,,0,0,0,,and it imports one -third of its goods.\N{\rChinese}并且其商品进口占三分之一。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.98,0:19:10.44,English,,0,0,0,,Food. It imports most of its oil.\N{\rChinese}食品。它进口大部分油料。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.30,0:19:13.70,English,,0,0,0,,These bonnet industries, EV,\N{\rChinese}这些帽子产业，电动车，
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.58,0:19:17.04,English,,0,0,0,,uh, AI, min, uh,\N{\rChinese}呃，人工智能，矿，呃，
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.12,0:19:18.40,English,,0,0,0,,rare minerals,\N{\rChinese}稀有矿物，
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.62,0:19:21.78,English,,0,0,0,,they're all contributing to massive\N{\rChinese}它们都在为中国的巨大
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.78,0:19:25.20,English,,0,0,0,,ecological destruction in China.\N{\rChinese}生态破坏贡献着
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.48,0:19:28.02,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, you can say it's unsustainable, but\N{\rChinese}我想说，你可以说它不持续，但也可以说这些经济政策，……又破坏环境，真是自杀式的，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.02,0:19:31.04,English,,0,0,0,,you can also say these economic policies that,\N{\rChinese}这些经济政策，……又破坏环境，真是自杀式的，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.04,0:19:34.54,English,,0,0,0,,um, destroy the environment, it's really suicidal, okay?\N{\rChinese}这些经济政策，……又破坏环境，真是自杀式的，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.62,0:19:37.58,English,,0,0,0,,So, so, China does not have a very bright future.\N{\rChinese}于是，中国的未来并不算太光明。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.98,0:19:40.70,English,,0,0,0,,It's not ahead of it. So Dugan's not worried about China either, okay?\N{\rChinese}它也没有领先。于是杜甘也不担心中国，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.92,0:19:44.04,English,,0,0,0,,So, um, that\N{\rChinese}于是，嗯，那个。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.04,0:19:46.76,English,,0,0,0,,is the master plan of,\N{\rChinese}是主计划，
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.76,0:19:48.86,English,,0,0,0,,um, Alexander Dugan.\N{\rChinese}嗯，亚历山大·杜甘。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.96,0:19:53.06,English,,0,0,0,,And again, it is based on the Orthodox eschatology,\N{\rChinese}再一次，它基于正教的末世论。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.30,0:19:56.24,English,,0,0,0,,which perceives Moscow as a third Rome\N{\rChinese}它把莫斯科视为第三罗马
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.24,0:19:59.16,English,,0,0,0,,and perceives Vladimir Putin as a last song,\N{\rChinese}并把弗拉基米尔·普京视为最后的歌声
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.20,0:20:03.68,English,,0,0,0,,as this great unifier of the world, of the world.\N{\rChinese}是这位伟大的世界统一者，世界的统一者
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.86,0:20:06.22,English,,0,0,0,,Um, in Dugan's terms,\N{\rChinese}嗯，在杜甘的说法里，
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.22,0:20:10.26,English,,0,0,0,,Putin is the catacomb, okay?\N{\rChinese}普京是坟墓，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.32,0:20:13.54,English,,0,0,0,,The catacomb is Greek word meaning the force that\N{\rChinese}坟墓是希腊词，意为力量
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.54,0:20:15.76,English,,0,0,0,,restrains the Antichrist, okay?\N{\rChinese}约束了末日之敌，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.88,0:20:18.32,English,,0,0,0,,So for Dugan, um,\N{\rChinese}所以对杜甘来说，好吧，
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.70,0:20:20.38,English,,0,0,0,,Moscow has responsibility\N{\rChinese}莫斯科承担责任
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.03,0:20:24.00,English,,0,0,0,,to be the force for civilization,\N{\rChinese}成为文明的力量，
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.40,0:20:26.28,English,,0,0,0,,for good, for God.\N{\rChinese}为善，为神。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.00,0:20:32.12,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, now let's move on to the last eschatological tradition,\N{\rChinese}好了，接下来是最后一种末世传统。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.38,0:20:35.58,English,,0,0,0,,which is the Catholic eschatology.\N{\rChinese}哪是天主教的末世论。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.22,0:20:39.36,English,,0,0,0,,Now, it's interesting because, um,\N{\rChinese}现在很有趣，因为，好吧，
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.22,0:20:42.96,English,,0,0,0,,if you read Augustine and the City of God,\N{\rChinese}若你读《天主之城》
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.14,0:20:45.38,English,,0,0,0,,what he argues is that\N{\rChinese}他所论证的是
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.38,0:20:49.02,English,,0,0,0,,the church is the millennium.\N{\rChinese}教会即千年
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.22,0:20:53.48,English,,0,0,0,,Um, the church is the embodiment of the Mesenian age.\N{\rChinese}嗯，教会是梅森时代的化身
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.74,0:20:56.98,English,,0,0,0,,So with the coming of the church, the world has ended because\N{\rChinese}于是随着教会的到来，世界就结束了，因为
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.98,0:20:59.48,English,,0,0,0,,the church is able to step out of history\N{\rChinese}教会能够脱离历史
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.00,0:21:02.80,English,,0,0,0,,and ensure peace, truth,\N{\rChinese}并确保和平与真理
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.96,0:21:05.36,English,,0,0,0,,and justice in the world.\N{\rChinese}和世界的正义。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.22,0:21:09.72,English,,0,0,0,,And that very much is still the, um,\N{\rChinese}而且这点仍然是，嗯，官方天主教会的主线。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.44,0:21:14.04,English,,0,0,0,,official Catholic church line.\N{\rChinese}official Catholic church line.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.62,0:21:17.58,English,,0,0,0,,Um, there are eschatological elements to,\N{\rChinese}嗯，有末世论的元素在……
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.74,0:21:19.90,English,,0,0,0,,um, the Catholic church.\N{\rChinese}嗯，天主教会。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.06,0:21:22.82,English,,0,0,0,,For example, uh, Catholics do believe that\N{\rChinese}比如，嗯，天主教会认为……
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.82,0:21:25.98,English,,0,0,0,,there'll be a second coming of Jesus, and there'll be some certain signs\N{\rChinese}将会有第二次基督再来，并且会有若干确定的征兆
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.98,0:21:28.86,English,,0,0,0,,that precede the coming of, the second coming of Jesus, which\N{\rChinese}这些征兆在第二次基督再来之前出现
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.86,0:21:31.36,English,,0,0,0,,include the masculine conversion of Jews, which\N{\rChinese}其中包括犹太人男性的转变
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.36,0:21:33.60,English,,0,0,0,,include the age of tribulation, which\N{\rChinese}包括受苦难之年，且包括，嗯，反基督的来临。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.60,0:21:37.00,English,,0,0,0,,include the coming of the, um, Antichrist.\N{\rChinese}但大体上，嗯，…。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.16,0:21:40.36,English,,0,0,0,,But for the most part, the, um,\N{\rChinese}But for the mostpart, the, um,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.42,0:21:45.12,English,,0,0,0,,Catholic church is committed to a policy of personal eschatology,\N{\rChinese}天主教会致力于个人末世论的方针，
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.36,0:21:48.86,English,,0,0,0,,which argues that it is for our own personal transformation,\N{\rChinese}其主张为个人转化之道，
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.02,0:21:51.72,English,,0,0,0,,our own personal salvation and redemption,\N{\rChinese}乃是为个人得救与复兴之策
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.08,0:21:54.76,English,,0,0,0,,uh, through the guidance of the church that\N{\rChinese}呃，通过教会的指引，能让世界更好。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.76,0:21:57.12,English,,0,0,0,,allows for a better world.\N{\rChinese}这就是官方说法，但我们可以。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.20,0:22:00.68,English,,0,0,0,,This is the official line, but we can,\N{\rChinese}This is the official line, but we can,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.68,0:22:04.84,English,,0,0,0,,we can be suspicious that this is actually what they really believe.\N{\rChinese}我们可以怀疑这才是他们真正的信念。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.02,0:22:08.58,English,,0,0,0,,Um, I'm sure that there are certain elements within the Catholic church\N{\rChinese}嗯，我确信天主教会内部有些元素确有末世论的世界观。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.22,0:22:13.80,English,,0,0,0,,who do have an eschatological, uh, worldview.\N{\rChinese}who do have an eschatological, uh, worldview.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.12,0:22:19.86,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And there are three reasons why I would think the church,\N{\rChinese}好的？还有三个理由，我认为教会……
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.06,0:22:23.02,English,,0,0,0,,uh, many elements in the church, um,\N{\rChinese}呃，教会里有很多元素，嗯，……
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.40,0:22:25.84,English,,0,0,0,,want radical global transformation.\N{\rChinese}想要彻底的全球变革。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.14,0:22:28.52,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So let's look at these three reasons.\N{\rChinese}好的？那我们先看这三个理由。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.80,0:22:31.28,English,,0,0,0,,First of all, we have to remember the origins of the Catholic church.\N{\rChinese}首先，我们要记住天主教会的起源。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.44,0:22:34.88,English,,0,0,0,,It started out as a secret conspiracy against,\N{\rChinese}它最初是作为对……的秘密阴谋而起。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.88,0:22:37.08,English,,0,0,0,,against the Roman Empire, and it succeeded.\N{\rChinese}对罗马帝国的阴谋，最终成功。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.50,0:22:38.70,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So\N{\rChinese}好？那么
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.70,0:22:43.02,English,,0,0,0,,the Catholic church is very good at conspiracies.\N{\rChinese}天主教会在阴谋方面非常擅长。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.14,0:22:48.10,English,,0,0,0,,In fact, it really developed the world's first intelligence agency,\N{\rChinese}实际上，它确实发展了世界上第一家情报机构，
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.44,0:22:49.98,English,,0,0,0,,first global intelligence agency.\N{\rChinese}第一家全球情报机构。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.78,0:22:53.38,English,,0,0,0,,Um, there are certain elements within the Catholic church,\N{\rChinese}嗯，天主教会内部有若干要素，
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.54,0:22:56.20,English,,0,0,0,,the Jesuits, Opus Dei, which are, which\N{\rChinese}耶稣会，Opus Dei，亦即…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.20,0:22:59.78,English,,0,0,0,,are famous for their effectiveness, their organization,\N{\rChinese}以其高效、组织闻名
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.22,0:23:03.00,English,,0,0,0,,um, their, um, strategy.\N{\rChinese}嗯，他们的，呃，策略。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.30,0:23:05.36,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So, um,\N{\rChinese}好的？那么，呃，
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.18,0:23:08.56,English,,0,0,0,,that's the first thing we have to remember about the Catholic church.\N{\rChinese}首先要记住的是天主教会的这点。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.76,0:23:10.92,English,,0,0,0,,They are very good at conspiracies.\N{\rChinese}他们在阴谋方面非常擅长。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.00,0:23:14.82,English,,0,0,0,,In fact, they're so good, we don't even talk about,\N{\rChinese}事实上，他们做得如此好，甚至连谈他们的阴谋都不说，
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.38,0:23:16.88,English,,0,0,0,,uh, their conspiracies.\N{\rChinese}呃，
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.06,0:23:19.78,English,,0,0,0,,So if you go online, on Twitter, on social media,\N{\rChinese}所以如果你上网，去推特，去社交媒，大家都在聊深层政府。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.42,0:23:23.18,English,,0,0,0,,everyone's talking about, uh, the deep state.\N{\rChinese}大家都在聊深层政府。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.36,0:23:27.28,English,,0,0,0,,Everyone's talking about the Jews. Everyone's talking about, uh, the state of London.\N{\rChinese}大家都在聊犹太人。大家都在聊，呃，伦敦的状态。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.36,0:23:28.70,English,,0,0,0,,But no one's talking about the Catholic church.\N{\rChinese}但没人聊天主教会。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.22,0:23:30.54,English,,0,0,0,,That's really weird.\N{\rChinese}真是奇怪。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.74,0:23:33.60,English,,0,0,0,,Uh, you have books and books and books of all,\N{\rChinese}呃，你有好多书，书，书，关于……
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.60,0:23:35.86,English,,0,0,0,,of, of how, uh,\N{\rChinese}呃，关于……
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.94,0:23:38.32,English,,0,0,0,,Jews have influenced history, but\N{\rChinese}犹太人影响了历史，但……
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.32,0:23:41.80,English,,0,0,0,,very few books on how the Catholic church influenced history.\N{\rChinese}关于天主教会影响历史的书很少。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.92,0:23:43.92,English,,0,0,0,,I would think that, um,\N{\rChinese}我想……
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.10,0:23:46.44,English,,0,0,0,,the most powerful,\N{\rChinese}最强大的
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.58,0:23:49.20,English,,0,0,0,,wealthiest, and\N{\rChinese}最富有的
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.20,0:23:54.04,English,,0,0,0,,most secretive organization in human history for the past 2,000 years, they would,\N{\rChinese}最秘密的
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.04,0:23:59.56,English,,0,0,0,,would have a much greater impact on human history than the Jews.\N{\rChinese}会对人类历史产生更大的影响，比犹太人更重要。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.98,0:24:02.96,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So, there's, like,\N{\rChinese}好的。就是说，像是，
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.96,0:24:05.66,English,,0,0,0,,something, something to remember about the Catholic church is\N{\rChinese}关于天主教会的事，记得有点要点。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.40,0:24:08.16,English,,0,0,0,,before the Anglo -American Empire,\N{\rChinese}在英美帝国之前，
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.22,0:24:10.66,English,,0,0,0,,they were the empire.\N{\rChinese}他们就是帝国。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.04,0:24:14.54,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? They had, they had 1,000 years from the fall of Rome\N{\rChinese}好的？他们从罗马陨落起已有一千年。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.50,0:24:18.30,English,,0,0,0,,until, uh, the rise of the, uh, British Empire\N{\rChinese}直到，呃，英国帝国崛起时
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.30,0:24:20.38,English,,0,0,0,,when they were in charge, when\N{\rChinese}当他们掌权时，当…
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.38,0:24:24.36,English,,0,0,0,,they were the de facto power in the world.\N{\rChinese}他们在世界上是事实上的强权
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.50,0:24:28.18,English,,0,0,0,,And for many, they believed that was the Mesitic age.\N{\rChinese}于是许多人认为那是米塞提时代。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.36,0:24:31.66,English,,0,0,0,,That was the millennium. That was the most perfect age,\N{\rChinese}那是千年。那是最完美的时代，
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.66,0:24:33.20,English,,0,0,0,,the most golden age in human history.\N{\rChinese}人类历史上最金色的时代。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.30,0:24:36.48,English,,0,0,0,,And we screwed it up. Uh, we threw it away, uh, with,\N{\rChinese}于是我们搞砸了。呃，我们把它抛了，呃，随着英国帝国的崛起。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.58,0:24:39.12,English,,0,0,0,,with the rise of the British Empire.\N{\rChinese}于是我们把它抛了，呃，随着英国帝国的崛起。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.32,0:24:43.04,English,,0,0,0,,And therefore, we, uh, must return to\N{\rChinese}于是我们把它抛了，呃，随着英国帝国的崛起。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.04,0:24:44.56,English,,0,0,0,,that golden age when\N{\rChinese}那黄金时代，当……
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.56,0:24:49.20,English,,0,0,0,,the Catholic church was the dominant empire in the world.\N{\rChinese}天主教会成为世界主导帝国时。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.44,0:24:53.80,English,,0,0,0,,And, um, the, um,\N{\rChinese}而且，呃，那个……
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.04,0:24:56.40,English,,0,0,0,,third thing to remember, remember about the Catholic church is\N{\rChinese}第三点要记住，关于天主教会的事是……
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.52,0:25:00.12,English,,0,0,0,,they really are the most powerful,\N{\rChinese}它们确实是最强大的……
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.12,0:25:04.08,English,,0,0,0,,powerful non -state organization in the whole world.\N{\rChinese}是全世界最强大的非国家组织。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.16,0:25:07.28,English,,0,0,0,,They have a global network. They have 1 billion followers.\N{\rChinese}他们拥有全球网络，拥有10亿追随者。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.92,0:25:10.08,English,,0,0,0,,If there is a global catastrophe,\N{\rChinese}若有全球灾难，
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.00,0:25:15.06,English,,0,0,0,,they are the most ready\N{\rChinese}他们最为准备。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.06,0:25:18.76,English,,0,0,0,,to rebuild the world after it collapses.\N{\rChinese}重建世界在崩溃后。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.18,0:25:23.54,English,,0,0,0,,So, these are major advantages for the Catholic church.\N{\rChinese}这些是天主教会的主要优势。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.76,0:25:25.86,English,,0,0,0,,And that's why I think that, um,\N{\rChinese}这就是我认为的原因，呃。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.94,0:25:28.78,English,,0,0,0,,there are many elements within the Catholic church who,\N{\rChinese}有许多天主教会内部的成员，
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.12,0:25:33.28,English,,0,0,0,,who do have an eschatological worldview.\N{\rChinese}他们确有末世论的世界观。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.46,0:25:36.46,English,,0,0,0,,They have a plan to conquer the world. And they are slowly implemented.\N{\rChinese}他们有征服世界的计划，并且正在慢慢实施。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.76,0:25:40.64,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So, having said that, let's go over the major opposition,\N{\rChinese}好的？说完了，接下来我们来梳理一下主要对手，天主教会的对手。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.36,0:25:42.94,English,,0,0,0,,the opponents of the Catholic church.\N{\rChinese}好吧，首个主要对手，当然是英美帝国。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.26,0:25:47.96,English,,0,0,0,,Well, the first major opponent, of course, is the Anglo -American Empire.\N{\rChinese}Well, the first major opponent, of course, is the Anglo -American Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.30,0:25:50.62,English,,0,0,0,,And the Anglo -American Empire represents, of course,\N{\rChinese}英美帝国当然代表着……
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.64,0:25:53.54,English,,0,0,0,,enlightenment principles, uh,\N{\rChinese}启蒙原则，呃，
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.30,0:25:56.50,English,,0,0,0,,neoliberalism, uh, materialism, capitalism,\N{\rChinese}新自由主义，呃，物质主义，资本主义
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.70,0:26:02.08,English,,0,0,0,,Protestantism. Okay? And remember, the Protestants and Catholics hate each other.\N{\rChinese}新教派。好吧？记得，新教徒和天主教徒互相仇视。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.24,0:26:05.76,English,,0,0,0,,Um, these are the two greatest rivals in human history.\N{\rChinese}呃，这两者是人类史上最大的两大对手。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.00,0:26:09.64,English,,0,0,0,,Their wars have cost millions of lives.\N{\rChinese}他们的战争已付出数百万人的生命。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.84,0:26:12.80,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So, that's the first major opponent to the Catholic Empire.\N{\rChinese}好的？所以，这就是对天主教帝国的第一个主要对手。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.32,0:26:16.08,English,,0,0,0,,Sorry, that the Catholic church must destroy.\N{\rChinese}抱歉，就是天主教会需要消灭的那一方。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.28,0:26:17.62,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The Anglo -American Empire.\N{\rChinese}好的？英美帝国。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.26,0:26:21.36,English,,0,0,0,,Second opponent is the nation state.\N{\rChinese}第二个对手是民族国家。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.66,0:26:23.76,English,,0,0,0,,Um, so, in Augustine's formulation,\N{\rChinese}呃，所以，在奥古斯丁的表述中，
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.82,0:26:26.78,English,,0,0,0,,the church is outside of history.\N{\rChinese}教会位于历史之外。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.86,0:26:28.92,English,,0,0,0,,It is above history. It controls history.\N{\rChinese}它位于历史之上，掌控历史。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.54,0:26:31.38,English,,0,0,0,,Um, but with the French Revolution,\N{\rChinese}呃，但在法国革命之后，
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.12,0:26:37.00,English,,0,0,0,,um, the idea of a nation state came into being.\N{\rChinese}呃，民族国家的概念才出现。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.18,0:26:39.56,English,,0,0,0,,And the idea of a nation state is that it is above church.\N{\rChinese}并且，民族国家的概念是它位于教会之上。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.10,0:26:44.34,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And that's why, in France, there is such an emphasis on separation of church and state.\N{\rChinese}好的？这就是为什么在法国，强调教会与国家分离。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.82,0:26:48.52,English,,0,0,0,,So, um, obviously, the Catholic church wants to reverse this order.\N{\rChinese}所以，呃，显然，天主教会想要逆转这一秩序。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.68,0:26:52.38,English,,0,0,0,,And in order to reverse this order, it really has to destroy the concept of the nation state.\N{\rChinese}为了逆转这一秩序，它确实需要摧毁民族国家的概念。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.88,0:26:55.20,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. And the third major opponent,\N{\rChinese}好的。第三个主要对手，嗯，是真正的现代主义。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.70,0:26:57.66,English,,0,0,0,,um, is really modernism.\N{\rChinese}嗯，是真正的现代主义。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.66,0:27:00.74,English,,0,0,0,,It is modernism in and of itself. The cult of the individual, uh, which\N{\rChinese}它是现代主义本身。个人崇拜，呃，哪一…
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.74,0:27:02.76,English,,0,0,0,,celebrates materialism,\N{\rChinese}庆祝物质主义，呃，哪一…
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.38,0:27:05.22,English,,0,0,0,,hedonism, pleasure,\N{\rChinese}享乐主义，喜悦，
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.94,0:27:07.92,English,,0,0,0,,um, multiculturalism.\N{\rChinese}呃，多元文化主义。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.28,0:27:11.78,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So, the church needs to destroy, uh,\N{\rChinese}好的？所以，教会需要消灭，呃，三方力量，若要恢复千年。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.54,0:27:17.02,English,,0,0,0,,all three forces, if it is to resume the millennium.\N{\rChinese}all three forces, if it isto resume the millennium.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.64,0:27:23.30,English,,0,0,0,,Um, and we can suspect that there is already a plan in place.\N{\rChinese}呃，且我们可以猜测已经有计划在进行。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.56,0:27:27.64,English,,0,0,0,,And, the Catholic church stands a very good chance of achieving its eschatology.\N{\rChinese}而且天主教会有很大机会实现其末世论。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.64,0:27:30.78,English,,0,0,0,,Um, so, let's look at the three signs\N{\rChinese}呃，先看一下天主教会的三大迹象
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.78,0:27:33.24,English,,0,0,0,,that the Catholic church is, has a plan in motion.\N{\rChinese}那就是它已经有计划在运作
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.50,0:27:37.36,English,,0,0,0,,Well, the current vice president of the United States, J.D.\N{\rChinese}好吧，现任美国副总统J.D. Vance，
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.36,0:27:40.10,English,,0,0,0,,Vance, he is a recent Catholic convert.\N{\rChinese}他是最近皈依天主教会的信徒。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.56,0:27:43.30,English,,0,0,0,,The new pope is an American.\N{\rChinese}新的教皇是美国人。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.52,0:27:45.30,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? I don't think these are coincidences.\N{\rChinese}好的？我觉得这不是巧合。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.62,0:27:49.38,English,,0,0,0,,Um, I think this is March, this is all part of a,\N{\rChinese}呃，我想这就是三月，这一切都是一部分的。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.40,0:27:52.04,English,,0,0,0,,uh, larger, uh, plan.\N{\rChinese}呃，更大一点，呃，计划。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.08,0:27:57.62,English,,0,0,0,,We also have to remember that the Catholic church is in very,\N{\rChinese}我们还要记得，天主教会现在非常，
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.46,0:28:07.60,English,,0,0,0,,very poor condition right now.\N{\rChinese}非常糟糕的状态。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.60,0:28:12.74,English,,0,0,0,,um, there has to be a way to trim\N{\rChinese}呃，必须有办法把那幅图裁剪一下
